SuperAdmin: Can access all data across all companies, including Admins and their respective users.
Company: Belongs to a SuperAdmin and has its own set of Admins and other roles (e.g., SuperDistributor, Distributor).
Admins: Have access to SuperDistributors, Distributors, and Retailers in their company.
SuperDistributors: Can access Distributors and Retailers within their scope.
Distributors: Can access Retailers and manage their data.
Roles: Define the level of access and permissions (e.g., SuperAdmin, Admin, SuperDistributor, etc.)